body.description: Improve your existing system’s performance with the Lexar NS100 2.5” SATA III (6Gb/s) SSD. This easy upgrade gives you faster boot-ups, application load times, and data transfers turning your old computer from dinosaur to dynamo with read speeds of up to 550MB/s. The NS100 SSD is shock and vibration resistant, and also has no moving parts making it cooler, quieter, and more reliable than a traditional hard disk drive. Available in capacities from 128GB-2TB so you can store your all your favorite files without unnecessary slowdowns. It comes with three-year limited product support.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Lexar SSD Review
reviews.reviewText: Rating: ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ (5/5)The Lexar SSD is a powerhouse storage solution that seamlessly combines speed, reliability, and durability. As an avid tech enthusiast who demands peak performance, I recently had the opportunity to test the Lexar SSD, and it did not disappoint.Performance: ⚡⚡⚡⚡⚡ (5/5)The standout feature of the Lexar SSD is its lightning-fast performance. With read and write speeds that exceed expectations, this SSD significantly reduces load times and accelerates data transfer rates. Whether you're working on large multimedia projects or gaming with high-quality graphics, the Lexar SSD ensures a smooth and responsive experience.Reliability: ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ (5/5)Reliability is a non-negotiable aspect of any storage device, and the Lexar SSD excels in this regard. The drive's robust build quality and advanced error correction technology provide peace of mind, making it an ideal choice for professionals who cannot afford data loss or downtime. The SSD's consistent performance over time is a testament to its reliability.Durability: ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ (5/5)The Lexar SSD's durable design stands up to the rigors of daily use. Its shock-resistant construction ensures that your data remains safe even in challenging environments. This durability, coupled with a sleek and compact form factor, makes the Lexar SSD a portable and dependable storage solution for users on the go.Compatibility: ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ (5/5)Lexar understands the importance of compatibility, and their SSD is no exception. The drive supports a range of devices and operating systems, providing flexibility for users with different setups. Whether you're a Windows, macOS, or Linux user, the Lexar SSD seamlessly integrates into your workflow.Value for Money: ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ (5/5)Considering its top-notch performance and reliability, the Lexar SSD offers excellent value for money. While it may come with a slightly higher price tag, the benefits in terms of speed, durability, and peace of mind justify the investment. The longevity and performance of this SSD make it a wise choice for those who prioritize quality.In conclusion, the Lexar SSD is a stellar storage solution that ticks all the boxes for performance, reliability, durability, compatibility, and value for money. Whether you're a creative professional, a gamer, or a tech enthusiast, this SSD is a worthy addition to your setup, providing a high-speed marvel that elevates your computing experience to new heights.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Works Great! If your cables work...
reviews.reviewText: I intended to install this as an extra SSD in my desktop. Unfortunately, this did not come with a data cable, which didn't seem like a big deal... I'll just zip down to Best Buy and get one! Did that. No problem, only when I tried to install it, the computer wouldn't recognize it! After fiddling with the cable setup, I decided to swap the new cable over to my working SSD. Sure enough, didn't recognize and wouldn't boot the computer. Bad cable... Replaced that, and now everything is just fine. Works well, data transfer speeds were identical to my Samsung SSD. No complaints so far!

reviews.reviewTitle: Expected performance and light. A good laptop hard disk replacement.
reviews.reviewText: The performance of this Lexar SATA SSD is as expected as seen on the benchmark I did. It was easy to mirror my current 1Tb laptop hard disk to this SSD and not only double my space but significantly boost performance for this storage. Installation was as simple as removing the hold device and inserting this one. How difficult to get to would depend on your machine though. Given the SSD is very light it does save a few grams. Then according to rating it should take less power as well.
